泰勒·斯威夫特 (Taylor Swift) 与格雷西·艾布拉姆斯 (Gracie Abrams) 在纽约闲逛：查看照片https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/taylor-swift-gracie-abrams-hang-out-photos-1235471622/Hannah Dailey Tue, 14 Nov 2023 19:11:23 +0000 MusicMusic NewsPop https://www.billboard.com/?p=1235471622 Both singers are fresh off receiving Grammy nods.<!-- do not apply CSS styles to this element! --><div class="pmc-paywall"><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <a  rel="noreferrer noopener"  href="https://www.billboard.com/artist/taylor-swift/"  target="_blank"  >泰勒·斯威夫特 (Taylor Swift)</a>在<a  rel="noreferrer noopener"  href="https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/taylor-swift-eras-tour-south-america-launch-argentina-celebration-post-1235470631/"  target="_blank"  >阿根廷</a>举行三场 Eras 巡回演唱会后回到纽约，看起来这位流行歌星在回家的第一个晚上是和她的朋友、经常担任开场表演的格雷西·艾布拉姆斯 ( <a  rel="noreferrer noopener"  href="https://www.billboard.com/artist/gracie-abrams/"  target="_blank"  >Gracie Abrams)</a>一起度过的。 </p><div class="injected-related-story // lrv-u-margin-tb-2 lrv-u-border-t-1 lrv-u-border-b-1 lrv-u-padding-t-050 lrv-u-padding-b-075 lrv-u-border-color-grey" ><div class="a-heading-border a-heading-border-background-color-grey a-heading-border-height-075 lrv-u-margin-b-075 lrv-u-margin-b-050@mobile-max"><h3 id="title-of-a-story" class="c-title  lrv-u-color-brand-primary a-font-primary-bold-s lrv-u-text-transform-uppercase lrv-u-padding-r-1 a-article-related-module-title a-article-related-module-title--color-brand-primary">有关的</h3></div><div class="o-card lrv-u-flex"><div class="c-lazy-image  lrv-u-height-100p"><div class="a-crop-3x2 a-crop-1x1@mobile-max lrv-u-height-100p"><img class="c-lazy-image__img lrv-u-background-color-grey-lightest lrv-u-width-100p lrv-u-display-block lrv-u-height-auto" src="https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/themes/vip/pmc-billboard-2021/assets/public/lazyload-fallback.gif" data-lazy-src="https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/gracie-abrams-press-credit-danielle-neu-2023-billboard-1548.jpg?w=237&#038;h=147&#038;crop=1" alt="格雷西·艾布拉姆斯" data-lazy-srcset="" data-lazy-sizes="" height="" width=""></div></div></div><div class="o-card__content lrv-u-flex lrv-u-flex-direction-column lrv-u-justify-content-center lrv-u-padding-lr-1 lrv-u-padding-lr-075@mobile-max"><div class="o_category "></div><div class="c_title "><h3 id="title-of-a-story" class="c-title  a-font-primary-medium-m lrv-u-padding-b-050 u-letter-spacing-0028@mobile-max">格雷西·艾布拉姆斯与泰勒·斯威夫特和诺亚·卡汉一起“尖叫”有史以来的第一次…… </h3></div><time class="c-timestamp  a-font-primary-medium-xxs lrv-u-color-brand-primary lrv-u-order-100" datetime="00:00-YY-DD-MM"> 2023年11月14日</time></div></div></div><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
>有人发现这两位歌手并肩行走在下东区，斯威夫特穿着白色连衣裙和海军蓝西装外套，艾布拉姆斯穿着棕褐色夹克和乐福鞋。 <a  rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow"  href="https://twitter.com/ChristianTs13/status/1724279429755519324"  target="_blank"  >推特</a>上发布的一段两人散步的视频显示，他们的一名保安大声喊道“走开！”一群狗仔队挡住了明星涂鸦的道路。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
>就在唱片学院宣布 2024 年格莱美奖提名几天后，二人组的夜晚即将到来。这位“反英雄”流行歌星和艾布拉姆斯都获得了点头。斯威夫特正在角逐包括年度歌曲、专辑和唱片在内的六项大奖，而这位《I Know It Won&#39;t Work》歌手则与 Ice Spice、Noah Kahan、Jelly Roll 和更多突破音乐人一起角逐最佳新人奖。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
>在<a  rel="noreferrer noopener"  href="https://www.billboard.com/music/awards/grammy-nominations-2024-list-1235468152/"  target="_blank"  >格莱美提名</a>生效的同一天，艾布拉姆斯向<em><a  rel="noreferrer noopener"  href="https://www.billboard.com/music/awards/gracie-abrams-first-grammy-nomination-taylor-swift-noah-kahan-interview-1235468695/"  target="_blank"  >《公告牌》</a></em>透露，斯威夫特是她最先庆祝这一人生愿望清单时刻的人之一。 “我和泰勒谈过，我们只是通过短信互相尖叫，比如很多全大写的： <em>Holy f–king s–t</em> ，”她说。 “显然，她应得的这一切，这一切，这一切。在庆祝职业生涯或任何个人危机的时刻，我都会给她发短信，所以能够互相庆祝这一点感觉非常疯狂。”</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
>除了获得格莱美奖提名外，斯威夫特还入围 2023 年公告牌音乐奖决赛，获得 20 个类别的提名。 BBMA 日期为 11 月 19 日；您可以通过<a  href="https://www.billboard.com/h/bbmaswatch/"  >BBMAs.watch</a>以及 Billboard 和 BBMA 的社交媒体渠道观看。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
>斯威夫特和艾布拉姆斯在 Eras 巡演的过程中变得更加亲密，后者今年早些时候<a  rel="noreferrer noopener"  href="https://www.billboard.com/lists/taylor-swift-2023-tour-artists-who-are-opening-for-her/gracie-abrams/"  target="_blank"  >作为开场</a>演出参加了一系列约会。这两位明星都称亚伦·德斯纳为亲密合作者，甚至曾经在辛辛那提的一场<a  rel="noreferrer noopener"  href="https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/taylor-swift-gracie-abrams-aaron-dessner-cincinnati-eras-tour-1235365746/"  target="_blank"  >令人惊讶的原声演出</a>中一起表演了艾布拉姆斯的《我想你，我很抱歉》。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
>下面是斯威夫特和艾布拉姆斯在纽约一起外出的照片： </p><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1240" height="1653" src="https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Taylor-Swift-and-Gracie-Abrams-nov-13-2023-nyc-billboard-1240.jpg?w=768" alt="泰勒·斯威夫特和格雷西·艾布拉姆斯" class="wp-image-1235471611" srcset="https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Taylor-Swift-and-Gracie-Abrams-nov-13-2023-nyc-billboard-1240.jpg 1240w, https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Taylor-Swift-and-Gracie-Abrams-nov-13-2023-nyc-billboard-1240.jpg?resize=225,300 225w" sizes="(min-width: 87.5rem) 1000px, (min-width: 78.75rem) 681px, (min-width: 48rem) 450px, (max-width: 48rem) 100vw" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">泰勒·斯威夫特 (Taylor Swift) 和格雷西·艾布拉姆斯 (Gracie Abrams) 于 2023 年 11 月 13 日现身纽约。 </figcaption></figure><figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1548" height="1024" src="https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/02-Taylor-Swift-and-Gracie-Abrams-nov-13-2023-nyc-billboard-1548.jpg?w=1024" alt="泰勒·斯威夫特和格雷西·艾布拉姆斯" class="wp-image-1235471627" srcset="https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/02-Taylor-Swift-and-Gracie-Abrams-nov-13-2023-nyc-billboard-1548.jpg 1548w, https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/02-Taylor-Swift-and-Gracie-Abrams-nov-13-2023-nyc-billboard-1548.jpg?resize=300,198 300w, https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/02-Taylor-Swift-and-Gracie-Abrams-nov-13-2023-nyc-billboard-1548.jpg?resize=942,623 942w" sizes="(min-width: 87.5rem) 1000px, (min-width: 78.75rem) 681px, (min-width: 48rem) 450px, (max-width: 48rem) 100vw" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">泰勒·斯威夫特 (Taylor Swift) 和格雷西·艾布拉姆斯 (Gracie Abrams) 于 2023 年 11 月 13 日现身纽约下东区。</figcaption></figure></div> ;
披头士乐队的“最后”歌曲“现在和那时”会留下什么遗产？ https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/beatles-now-and-then-hot-100- Five-burning-questions-1235471664/Eric Renner Brown Tue, 14 Nov 2023 18:48:10 +0000 Chart BeatMusicfive burning questionsMusic Newsrock https://www.billboard.com/?p=1235471664 This week’s Five Burning Questions looks at the Fab Four’s return to the top 10 of the Hot 100 chart.<!-- do not apply CSS styles to this element! --><div class="pmc-paywall"><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
>当年录制的歌曲如今已跻身前十名：披头士乐队的《Now and Then》让这位音乐传奇重新回到公告牌百强单曲榜的上游， <a  href="https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/taylor-swift-cruel-summer-number-one-hot-100-jung-kook-beatles-top-10-1235470495/"  >首次亮相就在本周的排行榜上排名第七</a>。 《Now and Then》被誉为披头士乐队的最后一首歌曲，最初由约翰·列侬 (John Lennon) 于 1977 年录制为小样，几十年后由保罗·麦卡特尼 (Paul McCartney) 和林戈·斯塔尔 (Ringo Starr) 完成，乔治·哈里森的吉他部分也融入到了最终曲目中。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
>随着首张专辑排名第七，《Now and Then》成为披头士乐队第 35 首进入前十名的单曲，也是他们 27 年来的第一首。从乐队目录的角度来看，“现在和那时”的未来会怎样？是否会有更多的经典艺术家尝试用更新的技术来复兴旧的演示？ <em>《广告牌》</em>工作人员将在下面讨论这些问题以及更多内容。 </p><figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"><iframe loading="lazy" class="youtube-player" width="640" height="360" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Opxhh9Oh3rg?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent" allowfullscreen="true" style="border:0;" sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation"></iframe></div></figure><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
><strong>1. 按照 1-10 的评分标准——1 分表示被压垮，10 分表示兴高采烈——考虑到围绕“披头士乐队最后一张专辑”发行的大张旗鼓，披头士乐队的粉丝们对于《Now and Then》首次登上热门 100 榜单第 7 名应该感到多么兴奋歌曲”？</strong></p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
><strong>埃里克·雷纳·布朗：</strong> 7？ 3？我不知道。就像<em>《广告狂人》</em>中唐·德雷珀 (Don Draper) 的“我根本不想你”模因一样——我怀疑歌迷们对披头士乐队在排行榜上的表现的投入程度，就像流行歌手对他们最爱的人的投入程度一样，而对于高管来说，他们对披头士乐队在排行榜上的表现的投入程度也一样。图表位置表明当前受欢迎程度或有助于未来成功的等式在这里并不相关。这是披头士乐队！我怀疑 Hot 100 的位置对他们或他们的粉丝来说有多大影响。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
><strong>吉尔·考夫曼：</strong> 5 – 必须给它一个中立的评级，因为，一方面，真正的披头士乐队必须对他们心爱的乐队的一首“新”歌曲没有获得第一而感到惊讶！在这个宇宙中，经过这么长时间的等待，这首歌怎么可能不登上全宇宙所有排行榜的榜首？话又说回来，在今天这里/今天晚些时候消失的音乐机器的流媒体时代，一个尘土飞扬的、机械操纵的、几十年前的一首昏昏欲睡的歌曲的演示，他们在上榜之前至少拒绝了一次，综合考虑，这是相当甜蜜的。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <strong>Jason Lipshutz：</strong> 8.《Now and Then》得到了高调的推出和发行，显然披头士乐队在文化上仍然是巨大的，但是，这仍然是一个精美的演示，最初是在 40 多年前录制的，所以是前 10 首首张专辑是相当了不起的。我只扣了两分，因为凭借《Now and Then》登上 Hot 100 排行榜第一名不仅对披头士四人来说是超现实的，而且还延续了他们在 Hot 100 排行榜上的记录——披头士乐队仍然拥有最多的歌曲排名第一的有 20 名，但每年，泰勒·斯威夫特 (Taylor Swift) 和德雷克 (Drake) 等现代艺术家都在接近这一目标。<br><br><strong>乔·林奇：</strong> A 9。作为披头士乐队的终生忠实粉丝，喜欢但不喜欢“时不时”，我仍然很高兴看到这个巅峰。在他们首次登上热门 100 排行榜冠军 59 年后，他们凭借一首新歌跻身前十，这真是太疯狂了。对它成为第一的希望有点不合理：周四发布意味着第一周的兴趣被分为两个跟踪期（因为每周图表每周五开始一个新的跟踪期）；另外，这并不完全是广播猫薄荷，而是比耳虫更忧郁的曲子。 （真的，有人认为这首歌值得成为披头士乐队目录中新的第一名吗？这首歌几乎受到圣经般的崇敬？）进入前十名——他们的第 35 次刷新纪录——是这首歌的完美巅峰。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
><strong>凯蒂·阿特金森：</strong>我会选择 7 作为第 7 号！是的，这是“披头士乐队的最后一首歌曲”，但也有很多因素对其不利，比如它的国际首映将于周四早上举行，几乎是美国排行榜跟踪周开始前的一整天。另外，这不是披头士乐队的一首乐观、流行的歌曲。是的，它很感人，但不像披头士乐队的热门歌曲或他们 90 年代发行的歌曲那样在旋律上令人难忘。考虑到所有因素，我认为首次亮相前十是一个巨大的胜利。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <strong>2. 《Now and Then》在第一周就以 1,100 万次播放量、210 万次电台播放量以及 73,000 首实体和数字单曲首次跻身前十。您认为这首歌会在一周内引起关注，还是会认为它会继续成为热门歌曲？</strong></p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
><strong>埃里克·雷纳·布朗：</strong>我以前就错了，但这感觉就像一周的关注爆发。我不认为自己是披头士乐队的痴迷者，但我确实是披头士乐队的忠实粉丝——听新版重新发行的所有演示的铁杆粉丝——而“现在和那时”感觉……完全无关紧要大部头书。目前，披头士乐队的声音也不完全符合时代精神。我不认为它会成为真正的热门歌曲，而且我也不认为顽固分子会听它足以维持强大的图表位置。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
><strong>吉尔·考夫曼（Gil Kaufman）：</strong>我认为这首歌很幸运能获得这些数字，老实说，考虑到围绕它的无休止的炒作，感觉很温和。请记住，一周前，泰勒·斯威夫特<em>1989 年的歌曲“From the Vault”（泰勒版）</em> “Is It Over Now（泰勒版）”首次亮相，获得了 3200 万次流媒体播放和 470 万次电台播放印象。是的，她是一位现代明星，但披头士乐队是永远的明星——所以考虑到反应不温不火，这首歌感觉就像是一种短腿的新鲜事物，在最初的炒作之后会慢慢褪色。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <strong>Jason Lipshutz：</strong>可能是一周的爆发，但由于我总体上喜欢“Now and Then”作为流行神器，我可以看到这首歌在流媒体和销售平台上表现良好，并为一些零星的广播剧打分，在接下来的几个月里。披头士乐队未发行的歌曲并不经常出现，而《Now and Then》可能会流行起来——也许不是作为新的热门歌曲，而是作为歌迷欣赏的图腾，它在他们的目录的流媒体和销售数据中占据了很长一段时间。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
><strong>乔·林奇：</strong>我不认为它会消失得无影无踪。当好奇和狂热的人们重新审视披头士乐队最后一首歌曲的承诺时，人们对这首歌的兴趣，以及它被收录在所谓的披头士蓝色专辑的扩展版中，将会持续下去。我认为它会继续成为“热门产品”吗？不。随着圣诞音乐逐渐蚕食百强单曲榜，而人们对这首歌的热情逐渐消退，它的百强单曲生涯将类似于吉米·尼科尔 (Jimmy Nicol) 与披头士四人组 (Fab Four) 的时光。<br><br><strong>凯蒂·阿特金森：</strong>我正在考虑一周的爆发，尽管我想象广播可能会以某些格式播放（也就是说，如果所有播放它的 AC 电台还没有切换到节日音乐）。顺便说一句，我希望披头士乐队的粉丝们也不会沉迷于上周推出的新红蓝专辑最热门歌曲的改版，因为这些经典歌曲的更新音频让人听起来像是第一次听到它们。如果“现在和那时”只引起一周的兴趣，那么这些系列应该成为下个月乃至未来几年受欢迎的节日礼物。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <strong>3. 你对《Now and Then》的期望是什么——现在你已经有一个多星期的时间来体验它了，你会说这首歌满足了他们的期望吗？</strong></p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
><strong>埃里克·雷纳·布朗：</strong>我没有任何期望。我们有那么多出色的披头士乐队歌曲，但它们却无处可去，而除了扩展的重新发行版之外，我从来没有认真考虑过获得<em>更多的</em>歌曲，这些歌曲有大量迷人的、古董级的演示和剪辑。我不能说我很失望，因为我对这首歌不抱任何希望。但我缺乏预期并没有让这成为一种默认的令人惊喜的情况。整个努力有一种恐怖谷的一面，这让我感觉很奇怪。如果这首歌足够好让我不再那么想的话，也许我会有不同的感觉。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
><strong>吉尔·考夫曼：</strong>了解我对这首歌的了解，然后了解其预发行的创作情况，这几乎符合我的预期。这不是启示，也不是圣杯，但它是有史以来最伟大的摇滚故事的美妙、甜蜜的尾声。它没有改变任何看法，也没有揭示任何具有纪念意义的东西，但最后一次听到列侬的声音确实很高兴。我并没有抱太大的期望，它也没有辜负我的期望。即使它亮起，也不会将其关闭，但也不会去寻找它。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <strong>Jason Lipshutz：</strong>我对“Now and Then”的期望相当低——它们通常是为了挖掘样本——所以让这首歌加入我的定期循环并沐浴在它沉思的美丽中是相当令人惊喜的。 《Now and Then》不是披头士乐队的经典，但它永远也不会成为经典。相反，我们有一系列可爱的旋律和豪华的制作，打包为 2023 年的尾声，但很可能会在未来几年作为迷人的深度剪辑持续存在。<br><br><strong>乔·林奇：</strong>作为一个以严峻的决心迎接人工智能辅助复活不可避免的冲击的人，我松了一口气。人工智能仅用于清理劣质磁带上的缺陷，而不是重新创建或模仿任何人的声音或吉他。 （顺便说一句，人工智能在 2021 年彼得·杰克逊 (Peter Jackson) 著名的纪录片《归来》 <em>(Get Back)</em>中的使用方式完全相同。）这首歌本身缺乏人们与披头士乐队联系在一起的直接旋律，即使是在他们的填充曲目中，但它在一首绝唱中很讨人喜欢。 -y方式。考虑到我的期望存在于恐惧和焦虑之间，我很高兴这首歌用意良好、执行良好且扎实。对于那些声称这是他们遗产上的污点的人来说，好吧，你显然不熟悉 1982 年令人厌恶的“披头士乐队电影混合曲”，这是一首国会批准的单曲，不知何故在热门 100 强单曲中排名第 12 位。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
><strong>凯蒂·阿特金森：</strong>我对它听起来是什么样子没有任何期望，但我很惊讶这是一首如此安静的歌曲。我现在明白为什么“Free as a Bird”和“Real Love”在 90 年代的歌曲中获得认可，因为它们更符合披头士乐队的一些流行歌曲，但我印象最深刻的是情感冲击力“现在和那时”。这部迷你纪录片的设置方式以及披头士乐队四位成员几十年来如何为这首歌做出贡献的背景故事是如此令人心酸。这感觉就像是来自一支乐队的一份意想不到的甜蜜礼物，他们真正欠歌迷的只是他们已经带给世界的东西。</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <strong>4. 考虑到《Now and Then》在 1977 年首次录制样片后就进入了前十名，并在几十年后借助新技术完成了制作，你认为我们会看到大量经典艺术家使用人工智能吗和现代软件来完善和发布旧材料？</strong></p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
><strong>埃里克·雷纳·布朗（Eric Renner Brown）：</strong>我完全预计会有大量涌入，尤其是考虑到将旧热门歌曲重新利用为新歌曲的浪潮。观众现在比以往任何时候都更加怀旧。很多经典艺术家都已逝去，而那些仍然存在的艺术家也不再年轻。但最终，我认为这种方法在图表上的长期成功并不比我们在重新发行时看到的淘汰转储更成功——也就是说，我并不认为它们会成功，真的。 Many truly great artists achieved that distinction in part through outstanding quality control, and I think that when listeners dig beyond what artists released, they quickly discover previously unreleased material was shelved for a reason. Put another way: The <em>Beatles</em> could only debut at No. 7, and with a solid song. What “new” song from a classic artist would have a bigger draw than a “new,” respectable Beatles song?</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <strong>Gil Kaufman:</strong> Probably, but this feels like such a unique, one-off kind of thing I hope we don&#39;t start digging into the crates for unfinished songs from beloved artists that won&#39;t significantly add to their legacies, if not outright despoil them. A good friend who is a major rock band manager once told me, “If they didn&#39;t release it as a single or even include it 11 tracks deep, you probably don&#39;t need/want to hear it.”</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <strong>Jason Lipshutz:</strong> Probably, although most of those attempts won&#39;t likely achieve the chart impact of “Now and Then,” simply because no other artists possess The Beatles&#39; timeless stature. If technology allows artists to revisit garbled or incomplete material and freshen it up, though, they should do it, by all means. Why leave something on the cutting room floor if you feel like you now have the tools and desire to make it presentable to the world?<br><br> <strong>Joe Lynch:</strong> Absolutely. Anyone pretending AI isn&#39;t going to change the reissue/remaster/catalog game has their head in the sand. I fear – well, let&#39;s be honest, <em>know</em> – that ethical questions about dead artists and AI will be secondary to profitability, but I&#39;m heartened to see that in this case, everyone&#39;s priorities seemed straight. AI was used to improve a worn-out tape, not to create anything new. Fingers crossed that those in charge of the estates of our late icons take the same care when using AI for potential future releases.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <strong>Katie Atkinson:</strong> It is exciting to think that this technology could salvage spotty archival audio from late legends, especially with the blessing of living collaborators and family members like in this case. I think hearing those two letters – “AI” – from Paul McCartney in an interview months ago scared a lot of music purists, but seeing this materialize feels like the best-case scenario for how the technology can be used.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <strong>5. Fill in the blank: the long-dormant artist who I&#39;d be most excited to get a “final” new song from would be _______.</strong><br><br> <strong>Eric Renner Brown:</strong> Robert Johnson… there have to be more 78s out there somewhere.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <strong>Gil Kaufman:</strong> Kurt Cobain. Duh. Despite my previous answer.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <strong>Jason Lipshutz:</strong> Daft Punk. If our favorite French robots unveiled one final dance single before officially hanging up their helmets, I would expect a full-on, five-alarm banger. Let&#39;s hope that they have even <em>more</em> than that for us someday, though.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <strong>Joe Lynch:</strong> Led Zeppelin. The reissues have shown us that plenty of material was left on the floor, and there&#39;s gotta be some bonkers Bonzo drumming out there that the remaining three-fourths of the band could finish off.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <strong>Katie Atkinson:</strong> Freddie Mercury with Queen. Knowing how active the band has remained, just wrapping up a new tour with Adam Lambert, the idea of getting to hear Freddie&#39;s restored vocals on one more bombastic Queen hit is very tempting.</p></div> ;
 Spotify Plans to Charge for Fraud: How It Works & Who It Affects the Most https://www.billboard.com/pro/spotify-streaming-fraud-penalties-how-it-works/Elias Leight Tue, 14 Nov 2023 18:44:14 +0000 BusinessStreamingspotifystreaming fraud https://www.billboard.com/?post_type=billboard_pro_post&p=1235471507 Labels and distributors will be charged 10 euros per song when Spotify determines the overwhelming majority of plays on a track are artificial.<!-- do not apply CSS styles to this element! --><div class="pmc-paywall"><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> Under Spotify&#39;s new royalties model, the platform will <a  href="https://www.billboard.com/pro/spotify-changing-how-pays-artists-stream-thresholds/"  >financially penalize labels or distributors</a> when it finds that more than 90% of streams on a song are fraudulent, charging 10 euros per offending track, according to several music distribution executives.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> The service&#39;s current remedies will also remain in effect — removing fake streams from the system so they don&#39;t impact payouts or charts, pulling the track off editorial playlists, and possibly striking them from the platform altogether. The fees racked up by labels or distributors will be charged against future royalties. </p><div class="injected-related-story // lrv-u-margin-tb-2 lrv-u-border-t-1 lrv-u-border-b-1 lrv-u-padding-t-050 lrv-u-padding-b-075 lrv-u-border-color-grey" ><div class="a-heading-border a-heading-border-background-color-grey a-heading-border-height-075 lrv-u-margin-b-075 lrv-u-margin-b-050@mobile-max"><h3 id="title-of-a-story" class="c-title  lrv-u-color-brand-primary a-font-primary-bold-s lrv-u-text-transform-uppercase lrv-u-padding-r-1 a-article-related-module-title a-article-related-module-title--color-brand-primary">有关的</h3></div><div class="o-card lrv-u-flex"><div class="c-lazy-image  lrv-u-height-100p"><div class="a-crop-3x2 a-crop-1x1@mobile-max lrv-u-height-100p"><img class="c-lazy-image__img lrv-u-background-color-grey-lightest lrv-u-width-100p lrv-u-display-block lrv-u-height-auto" src="https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/themes/vip/pmc-billboard-2021/assets/public/lazyload-fallback.gif" data-lazy-src="https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/market-streaming-fraud-billboard-2023-bb04-laurent-hrybyk-pro-1260.jpg?w=237&#038;h=147&#038;crop=1" alt="Market, Streaming Fraud" data-lazy-srcset="" data-lazy-sizes="" height="" width=""></div></div></div><div class="o-card__content lrv-u-flex lrv-u-flex-direction-column lrv-u-justify-content-center lrv-u-padding-lr-1 lrv-u-padding-lr-075@mobile-max"><div class="o_category "></div><div class="c_title "><h3 id="title-of-a-story" class="c-title  a-font-primary-medium-m lrv-u-padding-b-050 u-letter-spacing-0028@mobile-max"> Why Can&#39;t Music Fix Its Fake Streams Problem? </h3></div><time class="c-timestamp  a-font-primary-medium-xxs lrv-u-color-brand-primary lrv-u-order-100" datetime="00:00-YY-DD-MM"> 11/14/2023 </time></div></div></div><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> Like the rest of Spotify&#39;s new model, which also affects how the lowest-streaming acts and non-music noise tracks earn royalties, the new fraud rule will impact music&#39;s steadily growing “long tail” of tracks that don&#39;t get played much. In this case, it&#39;s simple math: Big artists trying to boost their numbers are unlikely to hit that 90% threshold for fraudulent streams since they already have an established audience that will listen to them. Any act with a fair number of legitimate streams would need a huge amount of fraud to trigger a penalty.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> This means companies that have built hands-off, high-volume distribution businesses with small margins, charging a small fee per upload — the three biggest are DistroKid, TuneCore and CD Baby — likely have the most to lose under the new rules. They have huge batches of new music uploading daily, and that means it&#39;s hard to know who is doing the uploading.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> Even so, Tunecore welcomed news of Spotify&#39;s change. “In order to effectively prevent bad actors from diluting the royalty pool for real artists with real fans, all companies need to be a part of the solution,” says <strong>Andreea Gleeson</strong> , the company&#39;s CEO. “We also have been engaged in a deep dialogue with all our DSP partners, including Spotify, to actively deploy anti-fraud measures that encourage content providers to make the proper investments to actually fight fraud. We are fully aligned with the measures that Spotify is implementing.” (Tunecore&#39;s parent company, Believe, has a history of publicly supporting Spotify initiatives, including Discovery Mode, which is unanimously opposed by the major labels.) </p><div class="injected-related-story // lrv-u-margin-tb-2 lrv-u-border-t-1 lrv-u-border-b-1 lrv-u-padding-t-050 lrv-u-padding-b-075 lrv-u-border-color-grey" ><div class="a-heading-border a-heading-border-background-color-grey a-heading-border-height-075 lrv-u-margin-b-075 lrv-u-margin-b-050@mobile-max"><h3 id="title-of-a-story" class="c-title  lrv-u-color-brand-primary a-font-primary-bold-s lrv-u-text-transform-uppercase lrv-u-padding-r-1 a-article-related-module-title a-article-related-module-title--color-brand-primary">有关的</h3></div><div class="o-card lrv-u-flex"><div class="c-lazy-image  lrv-u-height-100p"><div class="a-crop-3x2 a-crop-1x1@mobile-max lrv-u-height-100p"><img class="c-lazy-image__img lrv-u-background-color-grey-lightest lrv-u-width-100p lrv-u-display-block lrv-u-height-auto" src="https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/themes/vip/pmc-billboard-2021/assets/public/lazyload-fallback.gif" data-lazy-src="https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/02-Music-Fights-Fraud-billboard-pro-1260.jpg?w=237&#038;h=147&#038;crop=1" alt="Music Fights Fraud" data-lazy-srcset="" data-lazy-sizes="" height="" width=""></div></div></div><div class="o-card__content lrv-u-flex lrv-u-flex-direction-column lrv-u-justify-content-center lrv-u-padding-lr-1 lrv-u-padding-lr-075@mobile-max"><div class="o_category "></div><div class="c_title "><h3 id="title-of-a-story" class="c-title  a-font-primary-medium-m lrv-u-padding-b-050 u-letter-spacing-0028@mobile-max"> Digital Music Companies Band Together to Combat Streaming Fraud With New Task Force </h3></div><time class="c-timestamp  a-font-primary-medium-xxs lrv-u-color-brand-primary lrv-u-order-100" datetime="00:00-YY-DD-MM"> 11/14/2023 </time></div></div></div><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> “It&#39;s a positive incremental step to take, but it&#39;s incremental — you could see a service doing something much more drastic,” adds another senior executive. “It sends a good signal to the marketplace about intentions.”</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> On the other hand, DistroKid founder <strong>Philip Kaplan</strong> voiced his objection to the penalty system on a recent call with the Music Fraud Alliance, according to two sources who were also on the line. (Both DistroKid and Tunecore are members of the coalition.)</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> One of those executives described the gist of Kaplan&#39;s comments: “We can&#39;t determine if a new client is going to hire a marketing service that&#39;s going to bot streams until they&#39;ve done it. It&#39;s like you can&#39;t determine if your neighbor is going to commit a crime.” And the entity best able to monitor for fraudulent activity is Spotify itself. In this line of thinking, then, Spotify would be penalizing distributors for something that they didn&#39;t do, can&#39;t predict, and can&#39;t spot as quickly as the streamer itself.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> Kaplan declined to comment. Spotify also declined to comment.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> There is little public data on the prevalence of fraud and where it tends to occur. The most <a  href="https://www.billboard.com/pro/fake-music-streams-france-1-billion-2021-report/"  >comprehensive study</a> that&#39;s widely available was carried out recently by the Centre national de la musique (CNM), a French government organization, which found that “more than 80% of the fraud” detected by Deezer and Spotify in France in 2021 was “at the long tail level.” </p><div class="injected-related-story // lrv-u-margin-tb-2 lrv-u-border-t-1 lrv-u-border-b-1 lrv-u-padding-t-050 lrv-u-padding-b-075 lrv-u-border-color-grey" ><div class="a-heading-border a-heading-border-background-color-grey a-heading-border-height-075 lrv-u-margin-b-075 lrv-u-margin-b-050@mobile-max"><h3 id="title-of-a-story" class="c-title  lrv-u-color-brand-primary a-font-primary-bold-s lrv-u-text-transform-uppercase lrv-u-padding-r-1 a-article-related-module-title a-article-related-module-title--color-brand-primary">有关的</h3></div><div class="o-card lrv-u-flex"><div class="c-lazy-image  lrv-u-height-100p"><div class="a-crop-3x2 a-crop-1x1@mobile-max lrv-u-height-100p"><img class="c-lazy-image__img lrv-u-background-color-grey-lightest lrv-u-width-100p lrv-u-display-block lrv-u-height-auto" src="https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/themes/vip/pmc-billboard-2021/assets/public/lazyload-fallback.gif" data-lazy-src="https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/hacker-billboard-pro-2-2023-1260.jpg?w=237&#038;h=147&#038;crop=1" alt="黑客" data-lazy-srcset="" data-lazy-sizes="" height="" width=""></div></div></div><div class="o-card__content lrv-u-flex lrv-u-flex-direction-column lrv-u-justify-content-center lrv-u-padding-lr-1 lrv-u-padding-lr-075@mobile-max"><div class="o_category "></div><div class="c_title "><h3 id="title-of-a-story" class="c-title  a-font-primary-medium-m lrv-u-padding-b-050 u-letter-spacing-0028@mobile-max"> 1B French Streams Were Fake in 2021, Report Finds: &#39;Fraud Seems to Be Getting Easier&#39; </h3></div><time class="c-timestamp  a-font-primary-medium-xxs lrv-u-color-brand-primary lrv-u-order-100" datetime="00:00-YY-DD-MM"> 11/14/2023 </time></div></div></div><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> These acts are unlikely to be associated with a major record company, as the big labels focus primarily on the top releases: Odds are that many of the tracks involved in the fraud are there purely for that purpose — a bad actor uploads white noise or junk audio expressly to pump up plays with bots and attempt to extract royalties from the streaming ecosystem.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> Assuming that the 80% rule — or some semblance of it — holds more broadly across countries and streaming services, Spotify&#39;s new penalty system functions as “a direct shot at distributors that are just way overpopulating platforms with a lot of nonsense,” says another music executive with experience fighting fraud. In this view, Spotify is pushing distributors to look more closely at what it is they are distributing.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> “Being penalized should create an environment where the distributors will invest more to make sure that their business is cleaner,” says <strong>Ty Baisden</strong> , who manages Brent Faiyaz, among others.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> It remains notoriously hard to determine where streaming manipulation actually comes from.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> “Distributors might say it&#39;s the [fault of the] labels,” <strong>Ludovic Pouilly</strong> , senior vp of institutional and music industry relations at Deezer, told <em>Billboard</em> earlier this year. “The labels might say it&#39;s the management. And artists themselves might tell you it&#39;s the competition who&#39;s trying to negatively impact their reputation.” </p><div class="injected-related-story // lrv-u-margin-tb-2 lrv-u-border-t-1 lrv-u-border-b-1 lrv-u-padding-t-050 lrv-u-padding-b-075 lrv-u-border-color-grey" ><div class="a-heading-border a-heading-border-background-color-grey a-heading-border-height-075 lrv-u-margin-b-075 lrv-u-margin-b-050@mobile-max"><h3 id="title-of-a-story" class="c-title  lrv-u-color-brand-primary a-font-primary-bold-s lrv-u-text-transform-uppercase lrv-u-padding-r-1 a-article-related-module-title a-article-related-module-title--color-brand-primary">有关的</h3></div><div class="o-card lrv-u-flex"><div class="c-lazy-image  lrv-u-height-100p"><div class="a-crop-3x2 a-crop-1x1@mobile-max lrv-u-height-100p"><img class="c-lazy-image__img lrv-u-background-color-grey-lightest lrv-u-width-100p lrv-u-display-block lrv-u-height-auto" src="https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/themes/vip/pmc-billboard-2021/assets/public/lazyload-fallback.gif" data-lazy-src="https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/spotify-app-phone-2021-billboard-pro-1260.jpg?w=237&#038;h=147&#038;crop=1" alt="Spotify" data-lazy-srcset="" data-lazy-sizes="" height="" width=""></div></div></div><div class="o-card__content lrv-u-flex lrv-u-flex-direction-column lrv-u-justify-content-center lrv-u-padding-lr-1 lrv-u-padding-lr-075@mobile-max"><div class="o_category "></div><div class="c_title "><h3 id="title-of-a-story" class="c-title  a-font-primary-medium-m lrv-u-padding-b-050 u-letter-spacing-0028@mobile-max"> Spotify Is Changing How It Pays Artists </h3></div><time class="c-timestamp  a-font-primary-medium-xxs lrv-u-color-brand-primary lrv-u-order-100" datetime="00:00-YY-DD-MM"> 11/14/2023 </time></div></div></div><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> On top of that, there are also plenty of third-party marketing companies that artists hire thinking they&#39;re implementing legitimate streaming campaigns, but are actually just paying bot-farms to generate plays instead. This makes any attempt to assign responsibility for streaming fraud on a large scale fraught. “How are you going to hold a label or distributor responsible for something that they can&#39;t control at all?” asks an independent label founder.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> To that end, several distribution executives said they would try to shift any fraud-related penalties they incur on to whoever uploaded the music that was tied to fake streams. “Our plan is to pass on the fee to the accounts and the releases where it occurred to the best of our ability,” says one distribution executive.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> This offers its own challenges. If a fraudster already has money running through the distributors&#39; system due to previous streaming activity, or a legitimate bank account on file, the distributor might be able to claw back the penalty money it now owes Spotify when it learns of fraud. But if the fraudster recently signed up to the distributor, that might not be so easy.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> The biggest takeaway from Spotify&#39;s new policy may be that it demonstrates how much the conversation around fraud has shifted in less than a year. In 2022, no one would talk about it; in 2023, everyone is suddenly eager to tackle the problem — and to broadcast their efforts in a public manner.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> “Nobody&#39;s immune” to streaming fraud, <strong>Christine Barnum</strong> , chief revenue officer at the distributor CD Baby, told <em>Billboard</em> in April. “So people are finally having the realization, &#39;Yeah, this is a problem.&#39;”</p></div> ;
 Kim Kardashian Describes Explaining Kanye West Divorce to Their Kids: 'You Never Go to a Negative Side' https://www.billboard.com/culture/lifestyle/kim-kardashian-describes-divorce-kanye-west-children-1235471575/Gil Kaufman Tue, 14 Nov 2023 18:43:01 +0000 CultureLifestylekardashiansMusic Newsreality tv https://www.billboard.com/?p=1235471575 The reality star dove into the difficulty of splitting up her marriage and the impact her father, Robert Kardashian, still has on her 20 years after his death.<!-- do not apply CSS styles to this element! --><div class="pmc-paywall"><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> Divorce is never easy on the children. And when the two people splitting up are the most famous reality TV star in the world and one of the most well-known rappers on the planet — whose every move is dissected and chronicled by the tabloids — things get even stickier. </p><div class="injected-related-story // lrv-u-margin-tb-2 lrv-u-border-t-1 lrv-u-border-b-1 lrv-u-padding-t-050 lrv-u-padding-b-075 lrv-u-border-color-grey" ><div class="a-heading-border a-heading-border-background-color-grey a-heading-border-height-075 lrv-u-margin-b-075 lrv-u-margin-b-050@mobile-max"><h3 id="title-of-a-story" class="c-title  lrv-u-color-brand-primary a-font-primary-bold-s lrv-u-text-transform-uppercase lrv-u-padding-r-1 a-article-related-module-title a-article-related-module-title--color-brand-primary">有关的</h3></div><div class="o-card lrv-u-flex"><div class="c-lazy-image  lrv-u-height-100p"><div class="a-crop-3x2 a-crop-1x1@mobile-max lrv-u-height-100p"><img class="c-lazy-image__img lrv-u-background-color-grey-lightest lrv-u-width-100p lrv-u-display-block lrv-u-height-auto" src="https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/themes/vip/pmc-billboard-2021/assets/public/lazyload-fallback.gif" data-lazy-src="https://www.billboard.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Kim-Kardashian-cfda-nov-2023-billboard-1548.jpg?w=237&#038;h=147&#038;crop=1" alt="金·卡戴珊" data-lazy-srcset="" data-lazy-sizes="" height="" width=""></div></div></div><div class="o-card__content lrv-u-flex lrv-u-flex-direction-column lrv-u-justify-content-center lrv-u-padding-lr-1 lrv-u-padding-lr-075@mobile-max"><div class="o_category "></div><div class="c_title "><h3 id="title-of-a-story" class="c-title  a-font-primary-medium-m lrv-u-padding-b-050 u-letter-spacing-0028@mobile-max"> Kim Kardashian Reveals She Got a Tattoo in the Ouchiest Place Possible After Hosting &#39;SNL… </h3></div><time class="c-timestamp  a-font-primary-medium-xxs lrv-u-color-brand-primary lrv-u-order-100" datetime="00:00-YY-DD-MM"> 11/14/2023 </time></div></div></div><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <a  href="https://www.billboard.com/artist/kim-kardashian/"  >Kim Kardashian</a> dives into that uncomfortable talk in a new <a  rel="nofollow"  href="https://www.gq.com/story/kim-kardashian-men-of-the-year-cover-2023"  target="_blank"  ><em>GQ</em> cover feature</a> , in which she looks back at the lessons she learned from her father, OJ Simpson attorney Robert Kardashian, and dissects how he still inspires her to this day.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> Kardashian and her ex, <a  href="https://www.billboard.com/artist/kanye-west/"  >Kanye West</a> (who now goes by Ye) first filed for divorce in 2021, completing their split in November 2022 after marrying in 2014 and having four children together. The <em>GQ</em> piece explores how Kim&#39;s approach to the split was informed by the difficult divorce Robert Kardashian went through with wife Kris Jenner, something eldest daughter Kourtney said she knew about through the couple&#39;s “whisper arguing. My parents never fought my whole life, so it was traumatizing when they did,” she said.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> Kim, then nine-years-old — around same age eldest daughter North is now — never heard their fights, though, and when they called in the girls for a family meeting she said she “felt it.” She remembered her parents being “open” with them about the divorce, something she said she&#39;s tried to keep in mind for when her children might ask her about their parent&#39;s split.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> “Ultimately, what matters is that kids feel loved and heard,” she said. “You want to be sensitive because they&#39;re just kids, and it&#39;s hard to go through no matter what age. You have to make sure that you only go to a level that they can understand.表现出脆弱的一面是可以的。 You never go to a negative side.”</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> That said, restraint doesn&#39;t completely alleviate the emotional difficulty of divorce, which, in this case, was compounded by Ye&#39;s 2022 public meltdown, in which the rapper went on a <a  href="https://www.billboard.com/music/rb-hip-hop/kanye-west-antisemitism-experts-hate-speech-1235187544/"  >series of hateful antisemitic rants</a> and disturbing public pronouncements about Nazis that effectively melted down his once formidable $1 billion music and fashion empire.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> “Just because I know how to manage my stress well doesn&#39;t mean that I don&#39;t feel the emotions,” Kardashian said. “If I&#39;m sad, of course I will cry and feel it.”</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> The writer asked Kardashian&#39;s sisters and a longtime friend how she&#39;s changed since the divorce and they all pointed to a renewed confidence. “Not that she wasn&#39;t confident before,” said younger sister Khloé, “but it&#39;s a different assurance that she has in herself. She knows she can do it on her own. She knows the power that she has within herself, as opposed to thinking the power was in someone else&#39;s hands.”</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> Childhood friend Allison Statter added that Kim was “scared” to break up with Ye, “&#39;Cause deep down inside she wanted her family to stay together. And because she was like, &#39;I don&#39;t know what life is going to be like on the other side of this.&#39; I was just so proud of her.”</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> The piece also touches on how Kim was influenced to launch a men&#39;s version of her SKIMS shapewear line by her dad&#39;s sartorial taste and interest in menswear. “This man had style,” Kardashian said of her father, who exclusively wore Gucci when he began dating Kris Jenner.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> He always wanted to look cool,” she said, remembering him coming in to visit her at the trendy Encino, CA store Body when she worked there as a teen. “Diesel was one of the brands we carried. They had a cool pair of jeans. They were wax-coated. My dad&#39;s office was really close by, so he&#39;d always stop in. He said, &#39;I have to have those.&#39; I got them for him. He would wear them with just a black T-shirt and a loafer,” she recalled.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> Her self-made dad&#39;s entrepreneurial spirt, and insistence that his kids learn a work ethic, has been passed along to Kim&#39;s kids. As an example, she says North sets up a lemonade stand at the end of their street most weeks and hangs out for hours, using a clever sliding-scale payment method: $2 for randos, but sometimes $20 for people she knows. “I&#39;ll get calls from my friends saying she charged them $20 for a lemonade. She&#39;ll grab their $20 and say, &#39;I don&#39;t have any change&#39;,” Kardashian said.</p></div> ;
 For King & Country Extends Record Streak Atop Christian Airplay With 'What Are We Waiting For?' https://www.billboard.com/pro/for-king-and-country-what-are-we-waiting-for-number-one-christian-airplay/Jim Asker Tue, 14 Nov 2023 18:37:07 +0000 Chart BeatMusicChristian/Gospel https://www.billboard.com/?post_type=billboard_pro_post&p=1235471631 Plus, James Grear &#38; Company’s “I Wanna Say Thank You” rules Gospel Airplay.<!-- do not apply CSS styles to this element! --><div class="pmc-paywall"><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> <a  href="https://www.billboard.com/artist/for-king-country/"  >For King &amp; Country</a> , the duo of siblings Joel and Luke Smallbone, notches its 14th leader on <em>Billboard</em> ’s <a  href="https://www.billboard.com/charts/christian-airplay/"  >Christian Airplay</a> chart (dated Nov. 18) with “What Are We Waiting For?” The song increased by 7% to 6 million audience impressions Nov. 3-9, according to Luminate.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> The twosome extends its record streak to 11 consecutive Christian Airplay No. 1 singles (encompassing songs in lead roles promoted as proper, non-holiday radio singles, unless seasonal songs contribute to that run).</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> The siblings co-authored their latest leader.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> “Ever since I was a young boy, I&#39;ve loved music,” Luke Smallbone tells <em>Billboard</em> . “I never thought I&#39;d be a songwriter, but as I&#39;ve gotten older, I&#39;ve realized the true power of music – it can impact someone&#39;s eternal destination. For us to be a part of that journey in someone&#39;s life is an immense privilege and honor.” </p><figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"><iframe loading="lazy" class="youtube-player" width="640" height="360" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/f3LAHvGG2PM?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent" allowfullscreen="true" style="border:0;" sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation"></iframe></div></figure><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
>For King &amp; Country&#39;s 14 Christian Airplay No. 1s mark the second-most among all acts since the chart began in 2003, after MercyMe&#39;s 18. Jeremy Camp, Matthew West and TobyMac rank third with 12 each.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> “What Are We Waiting For?” follows for King &amp; Country&#39;s “Love Me Like I Am” (with Jordin Sparks), which ruled for two frames starting in February. Before that, the pair led with “Joy to the World” for a week in December 2022 and “For God Is With Us” for three weeks that July.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> The other No. 1s in the duo&#39;s active streak: “Relate,” which ruled for three weeks starting in December 2021; “Amen” (one week, July 2021); “O Come O Come Emmanuel” featuring NEEDTOBREATHE (two weeks, starting in December 2020); “Together” with Kirk Franklin and Tori Kelly (five, beginning in August 2020); “Burn the Ships” (five, starting in January 2020); “God Only Knows” (10, beginning in April 2019); and “joy.” (four, starting in August 2018).</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> Amid that stretch, the tandem&#39;s holiday track “Heavenly Hosts” reached No. 2 in January 2022. Plus, the duo featured on older sister Rebecca St. James&#39; “Kingdom Come,” which hit No. 26 that May.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> For King &amp; Country scored its first Christian Airplay No. 1 with its seventh entry, “Fix My Eyes,” for a week in September 2014. </p><figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"><iframe loading="lazy" class="youtube-player" width="640" height="360" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/fS55gvj3qqA?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent" allowfullscreen="true" style="border:0;" sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation"></iframe></div></figure><h2 class="heading larva //   a-font-primary-bold-xl   "> Grear &amp; Co. Get First Gospel No. 1</h2><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> James Grear &amp; Company&#39;s “I Wanna Say Thank You” featuring Maurette Brown Clark hits the <a  href="https://www.billboard.com/charts/gospel-airplay/"  >Gospel Airplay</a> summit. In the Nov. 3-9 tracking week, the song gained by 14% in plays.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> James Grear &amp; Company earns its first No. 1 in its second appearance on the chart, after “It&#39;s My Season” peaked at No. 29 in 2015.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> Brown Clark leads Gospel Airplay for a second time, after “It Ain&#39;t Over (Until God Says It&#39;s Over)” dominated for five frames in 2009. Her first of eight entries, “One God,” hit No. 2 in 2007, her first of four top 10s.</p><p
		class="paragraph larva // lrv-u-margin-lr-auto  lrv-a-font-body-m   "
> Brown Clark has an additional song on the Nov. 18 tally: “I See Good” ranks at No. 18, after reaching No. 14.</p></div> ;
